Title: Scale
JsName: scale
DataAttribute: data-scale
Category: Core
Description: Sets the zoom level of the rendered notation.
ShowInSideBar: false
Since: 0.9.4
---

<h2>Description</h2>
<p>
    AlphaTab can scale up or down the rendered music notation for more optimized display scenarios. By default music notation is rendered ad 100% scale (value 1) and can be scaled up or down by 
    percental values.
</p>

<h2>Types</h2>

<table class="table table-striped table-condensed type-table">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Values</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>    
    <tbody>    
        <tr>
            <td><code>float <span class="code-badge">all</span></code></td>
            <td>
                <code>1.0</code> -  100%<br />
                <code>1.2</code> -  120%<br />
                <code>0.8</code> -  80%
            </td>
        </tr>   
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Default Value</h2>

<code>1.0<code>

<h2>Example - C#</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-csharp line-numbers">
var settings = Settings.Defaults;
settings.Scale = 1.2f;
</code>
</pre>


<h2>Example - JavaScript</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-javascript line-numbers">
var settings = {
    scale: 1.2
};
var api = new alphaTab.platform.javaScript.AlphaTabApi(document.querySelector('#alphaTab'), settings);
var japi = $('#alphaTab').alphaTab(settings);
</code>
</pre>

<h2>Example - HTML</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-html line-numbers">
&lt;div id="alphaTab" data-scale="1.2"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</code>
</pre>
